article.headline: Longwood 78, Stetson 76
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. (AP) -- Kevin Swecker sank a pair of last-minute free throws and Longwood handed Stetson a 78-76 defeat Saturday. Longwood (4-12) traded baskets with Stetson (3-9) throughout the first half, and the score tied three times off shots from the Hatters' J.J. Hirst and the Lancers' Lamar Barrett. Garfield Blair added 11 to place the Hatters in the lead by five with 3:07 on the clock. Swecker added six to help the Lancers regain the lead, and Stetson trailed 33-31 going into the half. Mark Lohuis added 11 in the second half, putting Stetson up by as many as six. Ryan Bogan added a pair of free throws and Swecker followed with three seconds on the clock to gain Longwood the win. Kirk Williams scored 18 points for Longwood.
